President Cyril Ramaphosa is facing State Capture Inquiry on Wednesday. His testimony is being divided into two parts. eNCA's Tumelo Mothotoane and reporter, Siphamandla Goge are following this story. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa is set to testify at the State Capture Commission on Wednesday. Four days have been set aside for his testimony in April and May. READ: Norma Mngoma claims Guptas influenced SOE appointments The focus on the first two days of his appearance is on ANC issues and cadre deployment. He will then appear again next month to speak as the president of the country.